# =============================================================================
# PYTHONANYWHERE WEB APP CONFIGURATION INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================
# 
# 1. Go to your PythonAnywhere Dashboard
# 2. Navigate to Web > yourusername.pythonanywhere.com
# 3. In the "Environment variables" section, add each variable above
# 4. Set the Source Code path to: /home/yourusername/white-raven-pourhouse
# 5. Set the Working Directory to: /home/yourusername/white-raven-pourhouse
# 6. Set the WSGI configuration file to: /home/yourusername/white-raven-pourhouse/white_raven_pourhouse/wsgi.py
# 
# =============================================================================
# EMAIL SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================
# 
# For Gmail (recommended):
# 1. Enable 2-factor authentication on your Google account
# 2. Generate an App Password at: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
# 3. Use the App Password (16 characters) as EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD
# 4. Use your full Gmail address as EMAIL_HOST_USER
# 
# For other email providers:
# - Check your provider's SMTP settings
# - Common ports: 587 (TLS), 465 (SSL)
# 
# =============================================================================
# MYSQL DATABASE SETUP
# =============================================================================
# 
# 1. Create a MySQL database in PythonAnywhere Dashboard > Databases
# 2. Database name should be: yourusername$whiteravenpourhouse
# 3. Set a strong password and update DB_PASSWORD above
# 4. The database host is automatically: yourusername.mysql.pythonanywhere-services.com
# 
# =============================================================================
# DOMAIN CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================
# 
# Free subdomain: yourusername.pythonanywhere.com (automatically configured)
# 
# Custom domain setup:
# 1. Purchase domain (e.g., whiteravenpourhouse.com)
# 2. Add domain in PythonAnywhere Dashboard > Web > yourusername.pythonanywhere.com
# 3. Update DNS records at your domain registrar:
#    - Create CNAME record: www -> yourusername.pythonanywhere.com
#    - Create A record: @ -> PythonAnywhere IP (provided in dashboard)
# 4. Update ALLOWED_HOSTS above to include your domain
# 
